  "text": "Our proposed LBN-AA (shown in Fig. 5(a) ) is based on MobileNetV2 [CITATION_1] pretrained on the ImageNet dataset [CITATION_2] . MobileNetV2 is the latest lightweight image classification network, with the characteristics of fast speed, little computational time and small memory consumption. Note that MobileNetV2 is mainly developed for object classification, which substantially reduces the resolution of the input (the size of the output in the last bottleneck layer is only 1/32 of the original input image size and the final output is a probability vector). However, for semantic segmentation, we need to ensure that the size of output feature maps is moderately large (otherwise the spatial details will significantly lose). Hence, we appropriately modify the original structure of MobileNetV2 to serve as our baseline network.",
